  "title": "PROJECT MANAGER / EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p>Support the delivery of assigned projects by coordinating site activities, documentation, and stakeholders. This role focuses on execution and follow-up, with guidance from senior team members.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>• Coordinate day-to-day project activities and site matters<br />\n• Track schedules, progress, and basic cost items<br />\n• Prepare project documents, reports, and meeting notes<br />\n• Assist with PTW, insurance, and site submissions<br />\n• Liaise with contractors, suppliers, and internal teams<br />\n• Support QS with quotations and measurements<br />\n• Attend site and client meetings and follow up on actions</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>• Diploma or Degree in a construction-related discipline<br />\n• 2–3 years’ experience in interior fit-out or construction projects<br />\n• Basic understanding of site coordination and documentation<br />\n• Good communication and organisational skills<br />\n• Proficient in MS Office; AutoCAD is an advantage<br />\n• Reliable, detail-oriented, and willing to learn</p><p>CHANG Sze Yong (Eugene)</p><p>EA License No. 25C2923</p><p>EA Registration No. R1105304</p>",
